  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-01 trigger)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic adversarial package deliberately embeds two coexisting weaknesses on the same UnitOfAssurance: (a) the bound Claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom provenance link (W-EP-01, Critical orphan claim) and (b) multiple ValidationResults omit hasUncertaintyQuantification entirely (W-AL-01, High missing UQ). The combination triggers COMPOUND-01.",
